evidence: The WMoNbCrTi HEA prepared from 30 h milling powder shows the highest hardness value of 10.40 GPa.

The yield strength and fracture strength of the 5-HEAs reached the values of 2492 MPa and 2765 MPa, and the corresponding compressive strains were 5.6% and 9.8%, respectively, which are remarkably superior to the refractory HEAs fabricated by the vacuum arc melting.  11  The highest compressive strength of the HEA is attributed to the 5 h milling powder having softer and irregular particles, which are easy to contact and deform during the SPS process. As the milling time increased from 5 h to 40 h, the hardness of the HEAs first increased and then decreased, and it reached the maximum value of 10.40 GPa in the  30-HEAs.

The WMoNbCrTi HEA, sintered from the 5 h milling powder, exhibits the highest fracture toughness (7.16 MPa m 1/2 ), yield strength (2492 MPa), fracture strength (2765 MPa) and fracture strain (9.8%), respectively.
